DIRECTIONS for questions 1 to 3: Select the correct alternative from the given choices.

Who would the police have arrested?
ENGLISH.EASSY_DETAILS:
DIRECTIONS for questions 1 to 4: Answer these questions on the basis of the information given below.

In a shocking turn of events, a crime lord, Jaggubhai, was found murdered in his bedroom. The coroner determined the time of his death to be 10:45 PM. The police interrogated the neighbours and found that Ramlal, an old man who lived in the opposite house, saw all the persons who entered and exited the bedroom of Jaggubhai and he saw exactly five persons entering the bedroom of Jaggubhai on the night the murder took place. The five persons were Jaggubhai’s Servant, Butler, Carpenter, Driver and Secretary and the names of these five persons are Shiv, Kartik, Farhan, Gaurav and Bobby, not necessarily in that order.

The police were certain that whoever was in the room at 10:45 PM would have been the murderer and will definitely arrest that person. Further, it was also known that there was only one person in the bedroom apart from Jaggubhai at any point of time and none of the five persons entered the bedroom more than once that night. However, Ramlal, being forgetful, could only recollect the following information:

(i) Kartik exited the bedroom at 10:35 PM and Farhan stayed in the bedroom for 5 minutes.

(ii) None of the five persons was in the bedroom between 10:48 PM and 10:50 PM, after which only the driver entered the bedroom.

(iii) Bobby, who is not the Secretary, entered the bedroom at 10:40 PM and the Servant entered the bedroom at 10:30 PM, before Farhan did.

(iv) The first person to enter the bedroom was the Carpenter who entered at 10:25 PM and exited the bedroom at 10:28 PM.

(v) The person who exited the bedroom at 10:48 PM is the Secretary and the last person to exit the room was Gaurav.

ENGLISH.OPT4: More than one of the above
ENGLISH.EASSY_DETAILS:
DIRECTIONS for questions 5 to 8: Answer these questions on the basis of the information given below.

Captain Jack was marooned on an island which was a part of a group of three islands. The islands are called Bird Island, Cannibal Island, and Animal Island. There are exactly three types of people living in these islands – Truth Tellers, who always tell the truth; Liars, who always lie; and Alternators, who alternate between telling the truth and telling a lie, in any order. All the people that belong to a particular island are of the same type and all the people of a particular type are from exactly one island.

Captain Jack comes across three persons, Anderson, Bob, and Corey, but he does not know the islands that they belong to. He knows that there is at least one truth teller among the three persons and they make the following statements:

 

Anderson:

Bob is a liar.

This is not Cannibal Island.

I am from Bird Island.

 

Bob:

Corey is a liar.

This is Bird Island.

I am from the island that we are on.

 

Corey:

I am the truth teller.

There are at least two liars among the three of us.

I am from Cannibal Island.

The following information is known about their marks and ranks:

  1. The rank obtained by Lohit was numerically two more than the rank obtained by Akash.

  3. Lohit, who did not score the highest marks, scored more than Mohit, while Kiran’s rank was numerically more than that of Akash.

  4. The student who scored the highest was not ranked first.

During the final placements in a college, each of ten students secured three job offers, each from a different company. Each student has a dream company and a dream city in which he/she wants to work. Each student decides on the job offer to accept based on the following criteria:

  1. If one of the three job offers secured by the student is from his/her dream company, he/she will choose that offer, irrespective of the salary package that they provide.

  2. If none of the offers secured by the student is from his/her dream company, but one of the three job offers is from the student’s dream city, he/she will choose this offer, provided the salary package of none of the other offers exceeds the salary package of the offer in his/her dream city by more than Rs.2 lakh.

  3. If the student cannot choose any offer according to the above conditions, he/she chooses the offer which offers the highest salary package.
